cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and conversation generation. Additionally, the use of neural networks for addressing sparsity issues is a common technique in this field. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to natural language processing. The paper's focus on generative models and end-to-end training also suggests that it could belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it deals with the development of a software system. Finally, the use of information retrieval baselines suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
